//
// Two-core pipeline: shim -> A -> B -> shim. Core A is a 1:1 producer (no
// cyclostatic); Core B is cyclostatic on a_to_b (3-line sliding-window
// sum). Exercises cross-core cyclostatic sync on real hardware: B's per-iter
// `acquire(a_to_b, 3)` requires A to keep producing while B keeps consuming.
// Peel preserves B's per-iter acquire/release ordering on a_to_b so the
// producer-side lock drains correctly across iterations.
//
// REQUIRES: ryzen_ai_npu2, peano, xrt_python_bindings
//
// RUN: %python %S/aie2.py npu2 > aie.mlir
// RUN: %python aiecc.py --no-aiesim --aie-generate-xclbin --aie-generate-npu-insts --no-compile-host --xclbin-name=aie.xclbin --npu-insts-name=insts.bin ./aie.mlir
// RUN: %run_on_npu2% %python %S/test.py -x aie.xclbin -k MLIR_AIE -i insts.bin
